    "body": "Problem:  vim.ui_attach() msg_show callback runs the risk of a recursive\r\n          loop_uv_run() when trying to display a message from a shell\r\n          command stream.\r\nSolution: Schedule the message callback on the fast_events queue.\r\n\r\nFix #38664",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-06T08:07:24Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38737#discussion_r3032874870"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/38737"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3032874870"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This casts to `uintptr_t`, but `out_data_event()` casts to `intptr_t`.",
            "commit_id": "6b7ef7e30f181aa063f53bf194b0b7611e28bc23",
            "created_at": "2026-04-03T13:27:39Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -1121,33 +1133,24 @@ static void out_data_append_to_screen(const char *output, size_t *count, int fd,\n {\n   const char *p = output;\n   const char *end = output + *count;\n-  msg_ext_set_kind(fd == STDERR_FILENO ? \"shell_err\" : \"shell_out\");\n-  msg_ext_append = true;\n+  // Note: this is not 100% precise:\n+  // 1. we don't check if received continuation bytes are already invalid\n+  //    and we thus do some buffering that could be avoided\n+  // 2. we don't compose chars over buffer boundaries, even if we see an\n+  //    incomplete UTF-8 sequence that could be composing with the last\n+  //    complete sequence.\n+  // This will be corrected when we switch to vterm based implementation\n   while (p < end) {\n-    if (*p == '\\n' || *p == '\\r' || *p == TAB || *p == BELL) {\n-      msg_putchar_hl((uint8_t)(*p), fd == STDERR_FILENO ? HLF_SE : HLF_SO);\n-      p++;\n-    } else {\n-      // Note: this is not 100% precise:\n-      // 1. we don't check if received continuation bytes are already invalid\n-      //    and we thus do some buffering that could be avoided\n-      // 2. we don't compose chars over buffer boundaries, even if we see an\n-      //    incomplete UTF-8 sequence that could be composing with the last\n-      //    complete sequence.\n-      // This will be corrected when we switch to vterm based implementation\n-      int i = *p ? utfc_ptr2len_len(p, (int)(end - p)) : 1;\n-      if (!eof && i == 1 && utf8len_tab_zero[*(uint8_t *)p] > (end - p)) {\n-        *count = (size_t)(p - output);\n-        goto end;\n-      }\n-\n-      msg_outtrans_len(p, i, fd == STDERR_FILENO ? HLF_SE : HLF_SO, false);\n-      p += i;\n+    int i = utfc_ptr2len_len(p, (int)*count - (int)(p - output));\n+    if (!eof && i == 1 && utf8len_tab_zero[*(uint8_t *)p] > (end - p)) {\n+      *count = (size_t)(p - output);\n+      break;\n     }\n+    p += i;\n   }\n-\n-end:\n-  ui_flush();\n+  // Schedule to avoid recursive loop_uv_run() from vim.ui_attach() msg_show callback #38233.\n+  char *str = xmemdupz(output, *count);\n+  loop_schedule_fast(&main_loop, event_create(out_data_event, (void *)str, (void *)(uintptr_t)fd));",
